JOHANNESBURG (miningweekly.com) &ndash; Dual-listed Jubilee Platinum has been awarded a mining right for its 63%-owned, 22.3-million-ounce Tjate platinum group metals project, on the eastern limb of the Bushveld Igneous Complex. Describing it as a significant milestone for the company, CEO Leon Coetzer noted that the mining right confirmed the potential value of the project. &ldquo;The timing of the mining right coincides with the continued global recovery supporting the anticipated improvement in the platinum markets,&rdquo; he said. The company is now also required to issue 4.96-million ordinary shares at 1p apiece to its black economic empowered shareholder New Plats, as part of an agreement signed in 2009.